      <item>
        <title>Vector tiles</title>
        <link>https://nonlinear.nyc/vectortiles/</link>
        <guid>https://nonlinear.nyc/vectortiles/</guid>
        <pubDate>Thu, 06 Nov 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        <description><![CDATA[
          <p>## A SCSS mixin for vector tiles

Currently, we're playing with lines, others will come.

### Instructions

1. Download [vectortiles.scss](https://github.com/nonlinear/nonlinear.github.io/blob/main/assets/css/vectortiles.scss)
2. insert it on your SASS pipeline
3. follow instructions on file

### next steps

1. use other patterns (circles, crosses, and maybe more organic shapes)
1. what about color filters?
1. better presentation (organic shapes)
1. generalize mixin (maybe we can have just ONE mixin, with type of pattern using preset or create your own)
1. back to CSS? less dependencies

### digital artist?

Are you interested in creative code explorations? [Join us on
signal](https://signal.group/#CjQKIIdbvmNZ5REpZKHUq0T_2GY09uznGI3a0qqRgVEltNycEhCtQsqP5nSVyO_dKG5_dK81)
</p>
          <a href="https://nonlinear.nyc/vectortiles/"><img src="https://nonlinear.nyc/images/covers/vectortiles.jpg" alt="Vector tiles" /></a>
        ]]></description>
      </item>
      
        
        
        
        
          
          
          
          
        
